item.title: Let her go
item.description: You only need the light when it’s burning low, only miss the sun when it starts to snow, only know you love her when you let her go. Only know you’ve been high when you’re feeling low, only hate the road when you’re missing home, only know you love her when you’ve let her go. And you let her go. Staring at the bottom of your glass, hoping one day you will make a dream last, the dreams come slow and goes so fast.
